# Vercel Web Analytics Implementation

## Summary
Successfully implemented Vercel Web Analytics for the CyberOSINT Academy project. This enables visitor tracking and page view analytics on the Vercel platform.

## Changes Made

### 1. Installed @vercel/analytics Package
- Added `@vercel/analytics` version 1.6.1 to project dependencies
- Updated `package.json` and `package-lock.json` accordingly

### 2. Integrated Analytics Component
- Modified `src/App.tsx` to import the Analytics component from `@vercel/analytics/react`
- Added the `<Analytics />` component inside the main App function, wrapped within the GameProvider
- The Analytics component is now rendered on all routes and pages of the application

## Implementation Details

### Files Modified:
- **package.json**: Added @vercel/analytics dependency
- **package-lock.json**: Updated with new dependency tree
- **src/App.tsx**: 
  - Added import: `import { Analytics } from "@vercel/analytics/react";`
  - Added component: `<Analytics />` at the root of the application

### Technical Approach:
Since this is a React + Vite application, I used the `@vercel/analytics/react` package which provides:
- Seamless integration with React applications
- Automatic page view tracking
- Support for react-router-dom route changes
- Client-side tracking without additional configuration

### Placement Strategy:
The Analytics component was placed at the root of the App component (inside GameProvider but outside Routes) to ensure:
- Analytics loads once when the app initializes
- All route changes are automatically tracked
- No interference with existing routing logic
- Analytics persist across all pages and user sessions

